<HEADLINE> 4 Killed in Road Accident in Southern Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed on
Wednesday in a road accident in southern Egypt, the country's
Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The deaths were caused when a tractor and two trucks collided
on a desert road near Menia, capital of the governorate of Menia,
220 kilometers south of Cairo, security sources said.
</P>
<P>
The security sources did not give the cause of the accident,
which they said is under investigation. They did not specify the
number of the people in the vehicles, either.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents are common in Egypt due to high speed,
violation of traffic rules and regulations, and poor road
conditions.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released recently by Egypt's National Center for
Criminal and Sociological Research show that up to 6,000 people
die and 30,000 others are injured annually in traffic accidents in
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
