<HEADLINE> Canada Sending 200 Troops on Rescue Mission in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien said Wednesday that his country is sending 200 troops on
rescue mission in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the three-day Liberal caucus meeting in Halifax,
Nova Scotia, Chretien told reporters that the troops are to leave
in the afternoon and expected "on the scene within 48 hours", the
local media said.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government has also requested expertise in oil
fires and Canadian officials are consulting with experts who
helped extinguish oil fires in Kuwait, the media said.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 6.8 to 7.8 on the Richter scale atruck
western Turkey in the early hours on Tuesday, leaving hundreds of
people dead and many more trapped in damaged buildings. 
</P>
