<HEADLINE> Tanzania Opposes Dalai Lama's Attempt to Split </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's Minister of
Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation Jakaya Kikwete said
here Wednesday that his country is opposed to Dalai Lama's attempt
to separate Tibet from China.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania fully understands the Chinese government stand on the
Dalai Lama and will carefully handle the issue in the future,
Kikwete said while meeting charge d'affaires of the Chinese
embassy Liu Youfa who paid a courtesy call on him.
</P>
<P>
Development of relations with the Dalai Lama poses an action of
 animosity to China, he said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister added that Tanzania cannot afford to lose
an old friend like China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
