<HEADLINE> Kuwait Sends Relief Supplies to Quake-hit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Emir Jaber Al-Ahmad
Al-Sabah ordered on Wednesday to send urgent relief supplies to
Turkey's earthquake-hit areas.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Royal Palace said the emir ordered
the dispatchment of medical supplies, food, tents, clothes and
blankets to Turkey to help ease the sufferings of the victims of
the disaster, according to the Kuwait News Agency.
