<HEADLINE> 1,280 Kilograms of Drugs Seized in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1,280 kilograms of
narcotics have been seized over the past few days in different
cities of Iran's eastern province of Khorassan.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Republic News Agency on Wednesday quoted a law
enforcement forces official as saying that 11 armed thugs and
drug traffickers were killed during armed clashes.
</P>
<P>
The drugs include opium, heroin and hashish.
</P>
<P>
Since March this year, Iran's law enforcement forces have
seized 80 tons of different types of drugs across the
country. The figure shows an increase of 24 tons compared with
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Iran has been used as a transit route for shipping drugs from
neighboring Pakistan and Afghanistan to European markets.
</P>
</TEXT>
