<HEADLINE> Lesotho Chief Legislator's Body to Be Flown to S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The body of Lesotho
parliamentary speaker John Teboho Kolane is expected to be flown
to South Africa from Ghana on Thursday morning, South African
Press Association reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kolane, 73, died in his sleep at a hotel in Accra, Ghana's
capital, last Saturday night. He had been attending a conference
of African parliamentary speakers.
</P>
<P>
Family spokesman Mokhele Likate said Kolane's body would be
flown from Johannesburg to Bloemfontein, where it would be kept at
a private funeral parlor until it was taken to Lesotho for a state
funeral. The funeral was scheduled for Friday, August 27.
</P>
<P>
Kolane served as Lesotho's high commissioner in London between
1986 and 1989. 
</P>
