<DOCNO> XIE19990819.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HIV-Positive Rapists in Swaziland Face Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Rapists found guilty of
having infected their victims with the HIV virus could face the
death penalty once a bill becomes law in Swaziland, Deutsche Press
Agentur reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the new Public Health Bill, the death sentence
shall be given in compliance with the Criminal Procedure and
Evidence Act. It also stipulates life imprisonment for those who
knowingly transmitted the disease to their partners.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the death penalty and life imprisonment, those
convicted of transmitting the disease could also be forced to
compensate their victims to an amount to be determined by the
courts.
</P>
<P>
This also concerns persons convicted of other sexual offenses
including sodomy, indecent assault and incest that result in the
victims contracting the disease.
</P>
<P>
The act also provides fines for persons convicted of these
sexual offenses and in the process infecting others with sexually
transmitted diseases such as syphilis, gonorrhea, genital herpes
and HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The new bill will be debated in parliament shortly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
