<HEADLINE> No Improvement in Angolan Humanitarian Situation: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The humanitarian situation in
Angola, deteriorating due to the non-stopping civil war, shows "no
sign of improvement", according to a report reaching here
Wednesday by the United Nations Humanitarian Assistance
Coordination Unit (UCAH).
</P>
<P>
The humanitarian situation in Angola is still a very serious
problem for the Angolan government and the international
community, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The report, examining the humanitarian situation in Angola from
August 6 to 13, concluded that the continual "victim tides" have
made both the displaced people and the communities providing
assistance "vulnerable and impoverished".
</P>
<P>
It added that the humanitarian aid there also face serious
problems, with about 550 tons of food cried for per week in the
northern province of Malange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
