<HEADLINE> London Stock Market Ends Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 18 (Xinhua) -- London's leading index climbed
Wednesday, helped by strength in the electricity and
pharmaceutical sectors and Bank of England minutes.
</P>
<P>
After losing 1.2 percent over the past two session, its FTSE
100 index struggled back into positive territory and rebounded to
close 35.4 points, or 0.6 percent, higher at 6,201.8.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 350 electricity sector rose by 3.95 percent on the
back of National Power's 3 billion U.S. dollar sale of its Drax
Power Station.
</P>
<P>
National Power gained 22p, or 5.2 percent, to 448p, PowerGen
rose 20p to 590p and British Energy tacked on 42p to 530p.
</P>
<P>
The banking and pharmaceutical sectors also enjoyed gains.
Traders said both sectors are benefiting from interest rate
prospects, both here and in the U.S.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Xetra Dax index fell on the day as profit-taking set
in. The losses were partly triggered by a weak Wall Street opening
and came after the market's week-long rally.
</P>
<P>
The electronic index ended down 29.44 points, or 0.56 percent,
at 5,230.47 amid light turnover.
</P>
<P>
The rally in French shares stalled on the session, with the
benchmark CAC 40 index closing at 4,479 -- down less than 1 point.
</P>
</TEXT>
