venture and overseas training programs for some local employees
are mandatory," he said. "It is precious experience that Kenya
can learn from."
</P>
<P>
Kimkung said that China's economic cooperation and assistance
benefited kenya a lot.
</P>
<P>
The assistant minister also said China must remain one, and
that only China can decide its destiny.
</P>
<P>
The KANU delegation returned to Kenya's capital Nairobi
Wednesday, after a week-long official visit at the invitation of
China People's Friendship Association with Foreign Countries.
