<HEADLINE> Bourne Confirmed as Conservative Leader of Welsh Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Nick Bourne was confirmed as the
new leader of the Conservatives in the National Assembly for Wales
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The nine-strong Tory group in the assembly elected Bourne after
the resignation of former leader Rod Richards.
</P>
<P>
Richards had stood down temporarily from the leadership in
order to fight an allegation of causing grievous bodily harm to a
young woman.
</P>
<P>
His choice of deputy leader, 29-year-old David Davies, was then
rejected by the other Tory assembly members, who thought him too
inexperienced. Following the rejection, Richards later made his
resignation permanent.
</P>
<P>
Educated at the University of Wales, Aberystwyth, and Trinity
College, Cambridge, Bourne was the Conservatives' former chief
spokesman in Wales. 
