<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Locomotive Engine Derails </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A locomotive engine that
carries eight empty wagons has derailed the track, causing huge
economic loss to its owner Tanzania Railways Corporation (TRC), a
statement issued by the company said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place between Ngeta and Ruvu railway stations
in the eastern Coast Region when the locomotive engine was heading
from the capital Dar es Salaam to the Tanga Region in the north
earlier this week, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The engine derailed because a section of the railway was off
course after the bolts that hold together the tracks had been
deliberately loosened, it said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from setting the section of the track off course, unknown
people had also tried to unscrew bolts on other sections of the
railway track.
</P>
<P>
The statement further said that railways police unit has
already launched an investigation into the accident. They have
taken the accounts of the locomotive driver Mohamed Zuberi and the
police officer that was escorting the train.
</P>
<P>
According to the driver, shortly after the engine derailed he
saw three people quickly disappeared before any action could be
taken against them.
</P>
<P>
The TRC statement pointed out that the accident was planned for
the purpose of sabotaging the infrastructure of the corporation
and properties of its customers.
</P>
<P>
Following the accident, TRC has suffered a great loss, as the
corporation will have to meet the expenses of repairing the
damaged railway track, the engine and four wagons.
</P>
<P>
TRC also had to hire special buses to ferry passengers who were
stranded in Ruvu because the train they were travelling in could
not pass through the scene of the accident.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said that a passenger train that was to go
to upcountry on Tuesday was forced to postpone until 11 a.m.
Wednesday. Trips to and from Dar es Salaam by cargo trains also
had to be put to a halt for more than 10 hours.
</P>
<P>
The company has appealed to all citizens to be alert on people
who intend to sabotage the infrastructure of the corporation and
has urged people to take actions against these criminals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
