<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Insurance Co. Ltd. Restructured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Hong-Kong based China
Insurance Company Limited today announced its new leadership,
marking the end of its 10-month restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The restructured company, to be headed by Wang Xianzhang, now
becomes the holding company of all the overseas ventures of the
former People's Insurance Company of China (Group).
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1937 in Shanghai, the China Insurance Co. Ltd. is
one of the oldest insurance companies in China.
</P>
<P>
After the founding of the People's Republic of China in 1949,
it was taken over by the People's Insurance Company of China (PICC)
, later known as the PICC (Group).
</P>
<P>
In October 1998, according to an instruction from the State
Council, the PICC (Group) was broken into four companies, namely,
the China Life Insurance Company, the China Reinsurance Company,
the new PICC, which specializes in property insurance, and the
China Insurance Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The restructured China Insurance Co. Ltd. now has approximately
30 operational entities in Hong Kong, Macao, England, Germany, the
United States, and many other regions and countries worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Its business ranges from life and property insurance,
international reinsurance, and fund management, to securities and
investment, among others.
</P>
<P>
The company has total assets of 18 billion Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here today, newly appointed
general manager Wang Xianzhang said the restructuring was a result
of major reforms in China's insurance regulatory system, and a
strategic step taken by the Chinese government to promote
multinational operations by Chinese insurers.
</P>
<P>
Despite strong competition in the international insurance
market, he pledged that the new company will seek more diversified
operations while remaining with its traditional core business, in
order to make greater contributions to China's overseas insurance
business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
