<HEADLINE> hke081966 -Afghanistan Likely one of Most Mined Countries: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan is probably one of
the most mined countries in the world with an estimate of up to
640,000 mines laid since 1979, said a report of the HALO, a
charity organization specialized in the removal of the debris of
war.
</P>
<P>
In 1998 alone, HALO cleared over 100,000 individual items of
unexploded ordinances, mostly land mines, in its operations in
Afghanistan that was started in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Over 300 people a week were killed or injured by mine
explosions in Afghanistan, said the report. During a period of
refugee repatriation, the International Red Cross recorded 1,186
casualties from mines, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
