<HEADLINE> Former Aviation Official Sentenced for Bribery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Nanjing Intermediate People'
s Court Wednesday sentenced former director of the Jiangsu Branch
of the Civil Aviation Administration of China (CAAC) to 16 years
of imprisonment for bribery and embezzlement.
</P>
<P>
Cui Xuehong, 58, allegedly accepted bribes of 185,000 yuan and
1,000 U.S. dollars, and misappropriated 3.8 million yuan to
support profitable businesses operated by his friends between
January 1994 and January 1997, while he was director.
</P>
<P>
His graft also cost 1.79 million yuan in losses for CAAC's
Jiangsu Branch in east China.
</P>
<P>
His illegal income totaling 430,000 yuan was confiscated for
the State coffers, according to sources at yesterday's court
hearing. 
