<HEADLINE> Malaysian PM Hails Sino-Malaysian Relations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister Datuk
Seri Mahathir bin Mohamad said today that cooperative relations
between Malaysia and China have been strengthened and the efforts
made by the two peoples should be highly valued.
</P>
<P>
The Joint Statement on the Framework for Future Bilateral
Cooperation, signed by the Malaysian and Chinese foreign ministers
on May 31, will push forward further cooperation between the two
countries, Mahathir said at a reception in Beijing marking the
25th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations
between China and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said that this year is an historic occasion for
Malaysian-Chinese relations, and for China itself.
</P>
<P>
"China has made amazing achievements in the past 50 years,"
Mahathir said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, who also attended the
reception, said, "Sino-Malaysian friendship dates back to ancient
times. The two peoples began friendly contacts as early as 500
years ago."
</P>
<P>
"The two countries established diplomatic relations 25 years
ago, which opened a new chapter in the annals of friendly
relations between the two countries," Qian said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that all these achievements are the results of
the concerted efforts of the two governments and peoples.
</P>
<P>
"Over the past 25 years, China and Malaysia have upheld the
Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence as the basic guideline for
bilateral relations and have unwaveringly pursued a policy of good-
neighborliness and mutual trust," Qian said.
</P>
</TEXT>
