<HEADLINE> Premier on "Three Stresses" Educational Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- "Stressing political
consciousness" is the kernel of the current "Three Stresses"
educational campaign, and government officials of all levels must
deal with everything by taking a political view.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji, also a member of the Standing Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee Political
Bureau, made the remark here today while listening to a report on
the "Three Stresses": stressing theoretical study, political
consciousness, and healthy trends, in the State Council General
Office.
</P>
<P>
"Stressing political consciousness" means to persist in the CPC
's principle of "serving the people whole-heartedly," Zhu
emphasized, and urged all officials to strive for an effective,
hard-working, pragmatic, and clean government.
</P>
<P>
In his talk, the premier also condemned the Falun Gong cult,
saying that the battle against this anti-government group is a
serious ideological and political one, and said leading officials
at all levels must be unswervingly in conformity with the CPC
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Li Lanqing, vice premier and member of the Standing Committee
of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau, also spoke at the
meeting. 
