<HEADLINE> China Issuing 16 Billion Yuan In T-Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China has issued 79.4 billion yuan worth of treasury bonds in
five batches so far this year. The fifth batch would have an eight-
year term with an annual interest rate of 3.28 percent.
</P>
<P>
The interest rate would be calculated from tomorrow and be paid
on annual base, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The bonds would be allowed to be traded at the interbank
securities market and the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges at
the ending of the issue, it added.
</P>
<P>
