<HEADLINE> Prince Ranariddh Supports PM's Stance on KR Tribunal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian National Assembly
President Prince Ranariddh expressed Thursday his support to Prime
Minister Hun Sen's stance that foreign judges should not have a
majority in any joint tribunal with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Prince Ranariddh made the remarks upon his return from
Indonesia after a three-day visit at the invitation of his
Indonesian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
He told the reporters at the airport that it is a Cambodian
tribunal, so foreign countries must respect the sovereignty of
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
