national reconciliation and country's peace and stability, so we
must treat it (trial of Khmer Rouge leaders) properly and
seriously," Ranariddh stressed.
</P>
<P>
Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen Tuesday clearly rejected a
U.N. proposal for foreign judges to outnumber Cambodian judges in
any joint tribunal with the United Nations to try Khmer Rouge
leaders for genocide and crimes against humanity.
</P>
<P>
Under the U.N. plan, which is to be presented to the Cambodian
government next week by U.N. legal experts, the court would have
either five or seven judges, but Cambodia's judges will be in a
minority. 
</P>
