Information Minister Dapo Sarumi as saying on Wednesday that the
government will lift the five-year-old embargo on recruitment of
its employees, adding that the decision was to pave way for the
teeming unemployed youths that had suffered from the embargo
placed on employment.
</P>
<P>
He said that the decision on the 35-year age limit was taken to
curtail numerous cases of age falsifications in the service.
</P>
<P>
Conditions for retirement from the federal service were fixed
at 35 years of service or 60 years, whichever came first.
