<HEADLINE> Preparations for Philately Exhibit Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Preparations for the China World
Philatelic Exhibition are nearly completed and the organizing
committee has been receiving items for exhibit, Shi Weilin, a
committee official, said at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to open from August 21, the ten-day exhibition will
cover 42,000 sq.m of space at Beijing's International Exhibition
Center.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will include a total of 3,322 frames of stamps
and three display cases of stamps from private collections and
museums, including the world's first stamp, noted the committee.
</P>
<P>
Postal administrations from 39 countries, and stamp collectors
from 16 countries and regions will participate in the general
exhibit, and philatelists from 67 countries and regions will
participate in a stamp competition at the event.
</P>
<P>
Shi noted that this event will help promote the rapid and
healthy development of philately in China and the world, while
providing a venue for cooperation and exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Activities will include a gathering of young stamp collectors
and several seminars.
</P>
<P>
Shi also said that tight security measures will be taken during
the exhibition, but the activities of visitors will not be
disturbed.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China has some 20 million stamp collectors
across the country, the largest contingent of stamp-fanciers in
the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
