Northwest Territory "is still out of control," said the police
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The towering flame could be seen from 75 kilometers away, they
said.
</P>
<P>
There has been no report of casualties in the fire but 300
people have to be evacuated to nearby Rae.
</P>
<P>
The fire was fueled by high winds and dry conditions after
being started by a lightening storm across the region, reported
the media here.
</P>
<P>
The fire spread to five square kilometers within hours of
eruption and further grew to eight square kilometers Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
As many as 70 firefighters across the Northwest Territory were
called to fight the blaze, which has prompted municipal officials
to declare a state of emergency. 
