<HEADLINE> HK Business Forecasts Little Changes for 2nd Half 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong manufacturers
generally anticipate little changes in the volume of orders in the
second half of 1999 compared with the same period of last year,
according to a survey released Thursday by the Census and
Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Analyzed by the manufacturing industry, manufacturers in the
wearing apparel industry generally anticipate some drops in the
volume of orders in the second half of 1999 as compared with the
same period in 1998.
</P>
<P>
But on the other hand, most of the manufacturers in the
textiles, printing and fabricated metal products industries
anticipate a fairly stable volume of orders.
</P>
<P>
About one-third of the manufacturers in the electronic and
electrical products and electrical machinery industry expect a
mild increase in the volume of orders.
</P>
<P>
In general, manufacturers expect capacity utilization to remain
stable in the second half compared with the first half. Profit
margins are however forecast to be lower in the second half
compared with the same period a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
On export performance, exporters generally anticipate little
change to some decreases in the value of both domestic exports and
re-exports in the second half of 1999 compared with the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, these expectations made in the middle of 1999 are
more optimistic than those made at the beginning of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, most of the bankers also anticipate little change to
some declines in the value of total exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
