<HEADLINE> China's Civil Aviation And Foreign Funding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- China civil aviation has used
16.25 billion U.S. dollars worth of foreign funds since 1980,
according to the General Administration of Civil Aviation of China
(CAAC).
</P>
<P>
 Of that amount, 1.85 billion dollars worth came from foreign
loans, 500 million dollars worth from foreign investment funds,
and 13.9 billion dollars worth from leasing airplanes.
</P>
<P>
 China had signed aviation transport agreements with 78
countries by the end of 1998 and has over 40 airports open to the
outside and 190 international air routes to 40 countries and
regions in Asia, Africa, Europe, America and Oceania.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese airplanes can directly reach more than 57 cities
overseas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990819.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Universal Postal Union Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The congress is the most important meeting of the UPU and is
held every five years. Its major purpose is to revise UPU
regulations, discuss global postal development strategies, and
elect an Administrative Council and Postal Operation Council.
</P>
<P>
The congress consists of a plenary session and meetings of
various special committees, with French as the official language.
</P>
<P>
The host county of the congress is entitled to choose a doyen
of the congress, with the approval of the UPU International Bureau
and the Administrative Council. The doyen is generally chosen from
the international postal sector and holds the post of chairman of
the plenary meeting until the chairman of the congress is elected.
</P>
<P>
Asian countries have hosted two congresses, one in Japan in
1969, the other in the Republic of Korea in 1994.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990819.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Holding Int'l Confucius Cultural Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- China will hold a 15-day '99
International Confucius Cultural Festival in Qufu, Confucius'
birthplace in east China's Shandong province beginning September
26 to mark the 2,550th anniversary of Confucius' birth.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Qi, who is in charge of the organizing committee, said
that memorial activities, lectures, academic seminars, and
discussions of the economy, trade, science, and technology, will
be held during the festival.
</P>
<P>
He said that companies, groups, multinationals, and foreign
envoys will be invited to a three-day economic and trade fair of
the festival, but those are interested in Confucianism, including
Chinese and overseas politicians, distinguished scholars, business
delegations are welcome to a 21st century international academic
seminar.
</P>
<P>
Confucius (551 B.C.- 479 B.C.) is regarded as a great thinker
and educator in Chinese history. Confucianism, the school of
thought that developed out of his ideas, has had a great influence
on China's political, cultural and social life for thousands of
years.
</P>
<P>
The Cultural Festival which was started in 1984 has been
recommended by the National Tourism Administration. China Central
Television and Shandong's Star TV will televise the opening
ceremony of the festival live. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
