<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Govt Will Not Allow Aceh Independence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government would
not allow Aceh independence, Minister of Defense and
Security/Indonesian Military (TNI) Commander Gen. Wiranto said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said any rational aspirations of the Acehnese could be
discussed with the government.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto urged the separatist Free Aceh Movement (GAM) not to
raise its flag in the troubled province.
</P>
<P>
"Don't kill people, don't terrorize and pressure people, don't
kill security officers and don't destroy government and public
facilities and also don't raise GAM flag. If they surrender their
weapons, then we discuss what the Acehnese want. We talk," Wiranto
told reporters after a session with the House of Representatives
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of some 300 local political, social,
religious and youth leaders in Banda Aceh, capital of Aceh on
Wednesday, Wiranto said the military will declare a state of
emergency in Aceh if separatist rebels continue employing violence
and the situation becomes uncontrollable, he was quoted by
national newspapers Thursday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto's visit to Aceh came amid escalating clashes between
the military and the separatists, which have claimed hundreds of
lives on both sides this year and forced about 150,000 residents
to flee their homes.
</P>
<P>
The military has drawn fire for atrocities in the province,
especially during the Military Operation (DOM) period in
1989-1999.
</P>
<P>
President B.J. Habibie, who revoked the DOM status early this
year, has apologized for the military's brutality in the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
