<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Risky Investment Being Experimented With In Northern China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The first investment company
specializing in scientific and technological venture capital in
the western part of China was founded recently in the capital of
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The Xi'an New and High-Tech Risk Investment Company Ltd. was
set up with 50 million yuan (6 million U.S. dollars). It will
focus on the commercial and industrial use of high-tech
developments.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 80 percent of China's new high-technology
ideas remain on the drawing board and the contribution of
scientific research to China's economic growth is estimated at
below 30 percent, compared with 80 percent in developed countries.
Some analysts say that this wide gap is primarily the result of
insufficient funds and an unreasonable funding-raising system.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an has been seen as a potential "Silicon Valley" in western
China because of its concentration of universities, key state
research institutes, and industrial companies. The Xi'an New and
High-tech Development Zone had more than 2,000 high-tech
enterprises added over the past 7 years with combined earnings
from scientific, industrial and trade development this year of 20
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Jing Junhai, head of the zone's management committee, says that
the governments of Xi'an and various western provinces have been
doing their best to provide funds for high-tech development, but
companies still have difficulties getting adequate funds for
expansion.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
