<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Volunteers Testing Life Spent Entirely On The Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Some Chinese volunteers plan to
spend 72 hours in closely-monitored conditions with an electronic
network as their sole connection with the outside world in the
first experiment of its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
It is being sponsored by the Ministry of Information Industry
and other organizations to examine living with the country's
electronic network and domestic networking.
</P>
<P>
The volunteers will come from Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou
and are being chosen without regard to gender or age. They are
applying via the net and will be voted on by net-users, with the
final decision made by psychologists.
</P>
<P>
For the 72-hour period they will have to try to survive via the
net using 1,500 yuan in cash and 1,500 yuan in electronic currency
which is being provided by the sponsors.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry, China's networks have been
developing at a surprisingly rapid pace. In 1998, it had 2.1
million net users and that figure went to more than 4 million by
the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry is eager to learn how the network will affect
people's lives in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
