<HEADLINE> Japan to Grant $4.8mln to Tanzania for Debt Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two governments exchanged notes on the grant at a ceremony
held in the Ministry of Finance here Wednesday, The African
newspaper said, adding that it is meant to mitigate Tanzania's
economic constraints worsened by external debt.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's external debt stands at around 8 billion U.S.
dollars and the government leaders have appealed for debt relief
so that more financial resources could be used for the education
and health services.
</P>
<P>
The grant will also be utilized for economic and social
development through purchasing commodities necessary in various
sectors, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
