<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet Steps Up Building Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region in
southwest China has built a region-wide network of markets, which
play a pivotal role in bolstering economy on "the Roof of the
World."
</P>
<P>
A series of incentives involving provision of capital and tax-
reduction have been adopted over the past five years to beef up
construction of various types of markets, those of farm produce in
particular.
</P>
<P>
During the period, governments and concerned departments at all
levels have invested a total of 240 million yuan to build 117 farm
produce markets whose combined annual business turnover tops 1.5
billion yuan, 2.5 times than five years ago.
</P>
<P>
These markets has helped expand consumption in the agricultural
and pastoral areas, while conveniencing urban residents.
</P>
<P>
The booming markets also give a major push to growth of the
private sector in the region.
</P>
<P>
At present, Tibet has 40,000 self-employed households, with a
combined capital of 320 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The region's private enterprises numbered 253 with a registered
capital totaling 90 million yuan, and annual sales volume
amounting to 170 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
