<HEADLINE> Zambia to Adopt Forestry Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Parliament will discuss a
proposed law to ensure conservation and sustainable use of
forests, Times of Zambia newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Environment Minister William Harrington as
saying in an interview here that the forests bill also sought to
strengthen the enforcement of existing laws under the ministry.
</P>
<P>
If the bill is passed, Zambia would be obliged to implement
several global treaties like the Convention on International Trade
on endangered species of wild flora and fauna.
</P>
<P>
"The minister will have the right to declare endangered
species. This is definitely a very progressive bill," he said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that some 900,000 hectares of forest are
erased every year mainly for household consumption as firewood and
charcoal.
</P>
<P>
About 85 percent of urban households use charcoal and some
others use both electricity and firewood.  
</P>
</TEXT>
