<HEADLINE> National Flags Selling Well In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This year is the 50th anniversary of the People's Republic of
China and celebrations and a parade are scheduled for Beijing. The
Beijing Red Flag Factory, an authorized manufacturer, has sold 40,
000 national flags so far this year, according to Beijing Youth
Daily.
</P>
<P>
Some local people mail flags to relatives abroad so that they
can display the flag on National Day to show their love of the
motherland. The price has dropped 30 percent since May.
</P>
<P>
A 96 cm. by 64 cm. flag costs only 20 yuan. Small and medium-
sized flags are the best-sellers, especially the 15 cm. by 10 cm.
model. More than a million flags were sold when China resumed
sovereignty over Hong Kong in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Red Flag is now going all out day and night and is
producing a huge flag, 25 meters by 17 meters specially for the
National Day parage.  
</P>
