<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Move Lower in Tokyo on Weak Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower in Tokyo
Thursday, with export-oriented issues dampened by the U.S. dollar'
s weakness against the yen.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange dropped 12.52 points, or 0.07
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at to 17,879.74. The index
marked its first fall in nine trading day's.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, fell 3.08 points or 0.21 percent to 1,475.35.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 493.40 million
shares from 501.88 million shares Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Steel maker NKK was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented high-tech issues, which had been leading
overall share prices higher, were hit by the dollar's weakness.
</P>
<P>
At 3 p.m., the dollar was traded in Tokyo at 111.57-60 yen,
sharply down from 113.07-09 yen late Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's fall on Wall Street, where the Dow Jones Industrial
Average marked its first decline in six trading days, was another
factor leading Tokyo share prices lower, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Despite the decline in the Nikkei index, traders remained
optimistic about the course of Tokyo share prices, saying the yen'
s strength reflects the recovery in the Japanese economy.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outnumbered
gainers 729 to 364, with 183 issues ending unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
