<HEADLINE> Kenyan Government Urged to Further Curb Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 19 (Xinhua) -- A Kenya's major newspaper
Thursday urged the government to take tough measures to curb bank
robberies.
</P>
<P>
The Daily Nation mentioned in a commentary that recently six
robbers singing hymns took over a bank for three hours, robbing a
total of nine million shillings (about 121,000 U.S. dollars) from
bank workers and customers.
</P>
<P>
"It was the worst ridicule of our security apparatus in recent
times," the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
It said that the recent spate of bank robberies, two of which
had occurred in broad daylight on Kenyatta Avenue, with the
criminals displaying an aura of calmness and bravado, had not
done the police image any good, noting that similar robberies had
also happened in other towns.
</P>
<P>
Until the police keep the criminals at bay, there will be
widespread panic among the public and law and order will break
down, the article warns.
</P>
<P>
However, the commentary admits that police alone could not
eliminate crime and called on the public to provide tips to the
police.
</P>
<P>
According to Kenyan Police, crime cases in the first half of
this year were on a decline compared to those in the same period
of last year. 
</P>
