<HEADLINE> China Spending More On Anti-Drug War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government has promised to provide substantial manpower,
materials, and financial support for the anti-drug campaign.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, Chinese police dealt with more
than 110,000 cases related to drugs and arrested more than 140,000
people for involvement in the drug business.
</P>
<P>
China has increased efforts to combat narcotics since 1997 and
has achieved some good results, the official says, with 15.4 tons
of heroin and 3.9 tons of "ice" seized over the past two and a
half years. But, in spite of this, he says, the better equipped
drug dealers still pose a serious threat to social security and to
people's lives.
</P>
