<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Minister Speaks About International Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan,
in a report on the international situation and China's diplomatic
work to senior Party and government officials and military
officers here today, said that the trend toward relaxation in
international affairs has not changed and that peace and
development are the two main topics now.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting organized by the Publicity Department of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and other departments,
Tang said that there have been important changes in the
international situation and international relations this year and
today's world is still not peaceful and tranquil and that factors
of instability, uncertainty, and unrest in politics and the
economy and the number of regional ethnic and religious conflicts
and territorial disputes have been increasing. Hegemonism and
power politics are having new development and the issue of
military security is still conspicuous.
</P>
<P>
But, Tang said, there are more opportunities and hopes rather
than challenges and difficulties in the international situation
China is getting involved. He said that the powerfulness and
prosperity of the country provides strong backing for diplomacy
and to maintain social and political stability and develop the
economy in a sustainable, fast and healthy way is the fundamental
guarantee for diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
In the complicated international situation, he said, China will,
under the leadership of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party with Jiang Zemin at the core, adhere to Deng Xiaoping's
ideas on diplomacy, firmly implement its independent foreign
policy of peace, safeguard sovereignty, territorial integrity, and
national dignity, and oppose hegemonism and safeguard world peace
to promote the common development of human beings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
