<HEADLINE> South China Province Maintains Steady Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Economy was on a path of
steady development in South China's Guangdong Province in July,
with fast-paced growth in production and marketing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, investment, consumption and exports maintained an
upbeat trend, indicating a strong force driving the local economy.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the province spent 93.8 billion
yuan in capital construction, technical renovations and real
estate development in the first seven months of the year, up 22.7
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales of consumer commodities exceeded 200.7 billion
yuan from January to July, a rise of nine percent. And the decline
of exports was reversed in July. Total exports stood at 39.41
billion U.S. dollars during the first seven months.
</P>
<P>
In the January-July period, the province jacked up 137.9
billion yuan in industrial added value, a rise of 13.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
A senior local official has called for greater efforts to meet
the province's goal of achieving an 8.5-percent growth rate this
year. 
