<HEADLINE> Earthquake Toll Exceeds 4,000 in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of the strong
earthquake in Turkey's northwestern region reached 4,053 while the
number of injured reached 18,352 by 5:00 a.m. local time Thursday
(0200 GMT), said the government crisis center in Ankara.
</P>
<P>
In a statement broadcast by the Turkish state television, the
center said that 2,080 people were killed and 4,892 injured in
Izmit, where the epicenter was located.
</P>
<P>
Severe casualties were reported in neighboring Sakarya, Yalova
and Istanbul, while five provinces were also affected by the quake,
which measured 7.4 on the open-ended Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
The tremor hit Turkey at 3:02 a.m. (0002 GMT) on Tuesday and
lasted some 45 seconds when people were sleeping in bed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
