<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico to Maintain Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's economy will grow 3.
6 percent in the third quarter of the year and 3.9 percent in the
final quarter, forecasts a U.S. financial analysis company, Morgan
Stanley Dean Witter.
</P>
<P>
A 3.2 percent growth in the second quarter in Mexico "created a
solid base for a second semester even more prosperous," said the
company in a statement published on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The stability of Mexico's exports to the United States, the
rise in petroleum prices which strengthens Mexico's finance and
the recovery of internal consumption contributed to the growth of
Mexico's gross domestic product (GDP), added the company.
</P>
<P>
The financial authorities in Mexico forecast that the country
will close the year with a growth of 3 percent and an inflation
rate of 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, local analysts said Mexico will also see an
increasingly uneven distribution of income, because growth will be
insufficient to eliminate the problem of high unemployment.
</P>
<P>
Ten percent of Mexicans currently control 34 percent of the
country's wealth. By 2025, the top 10 percent will control half of
the nation's wealth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
