<HEADLINE> At Least 260,000 Mexicans Tested HIV Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 18 (Xinhua) -- At least 260,000 people in
Mexico are carriers of the HIV virus, which causes AIDS, a local
human rights center said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The real figure of HIV cases in the country surpasses the
official one due to the delay or absence of registrations, while
130,000 infected people receive little or no medical attention,
said Edgar Cortes Morales, of the Human Rights Center Agustin Pro
Juarez.
</P>
<P>
He said that of the almost 59,000 registered cases of HIV in
Mexico, half of them have developed full-blown AIDS.
</P>
<P>
This is not just cold and anonymous figures, but about real
people, Cortes said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
