<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Semisynthetic Antibiotic Base Built in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUAN, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The new production line of
the Sino-Japanese venture Beida Corp. Ltd. has been put into
operation, making Huabei Pharmaceutical Factory the largest
semisynthetic antibiotic base in Asia with an annual output of 1,
200 tons.
</P>
<P>
Beida, located in Shijiazhuang, capital of Hebei Province in
north China, costs 59.99 million U.S. dollars and boasts the state-
of-the-art equipment in its key production lines.
</P>
<P>
Huabei Pharmaceutical Factory, the largest in Asia, is the
country's leading producer of antibiotics, raw semisynthetic
antibiotic and related products.  
