<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Draws Croatia 0-0 in Euro Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia and Croatia had a
goalless draw in a European 2000 qualifier here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The result leaves Yugoslavia top of group eight with 10 points
from four games, one point ahead of Ireland. Croatia are third
with eight points from five matches and next takes on Malta on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia and Croatia will play in Dublin on September 1.
</P>
<P>
Predrag Mijatovic almost gave Yugoslavia the lead in the
opening minute when he hit the post from close range, but the
visitors settled down mid-way through the first half and were
denied by the woodwork themselves twice before the interval.
</P>
<P>
Striker Davor Suker hit the upright from a narrow angle after a
quick breakaway and Yugoslav defender Sinisa Mihajlovic was spared
an own goal when he deflected the ball past his own keeper
Aleksandar Kocic in the 31st minute but saw it come back off the
bar.
</P>
<P>
Dejan Stankovic also came close for Yugoslavia when he forced a
brilliant save from Croatian keeper Drazen Ladic with a 25-yard
scorcher.
</P>
<P>
Aljosa Asanovic and Robert Jarni nearly gave Croatia a win
which would have put them top of group eight but Kocic blocked two
shots with the Yugoslav defence well beaten. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
