<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange closed down 1.64 percnet to 472.46
points on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover slided from Tuesday's 18.53 million dollars to 16.
36 million dollars only.
</P>
<P>
The interbank rate of interest increased to 5.6 percent in the
24-hour term against 5.5 percent on Tuesday. The parity of the
peso against the dollar remained unchanged at 0.997 for purchase
and 1.002 for sale. 
