<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Opening Ceremony Boosts Tibetan Culture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- No sophisticated technology, no
dazzling audio-visual effects, but the opening ceremony of the
sixth national ethnic games impressed the spectators to the same
effect.
</P>
<P>
"The Tibet Autonomous Region (TAG) is incompatible with the
inland provinces as far as the finance is concerned, we cannot
afford the big-spending hi-tech devices, so we need to give full
display to the Tibetan culture to our advantage." said Danzeng
Gongbu, the general masterminder of the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony has been hailed as the showwindow of the
Tibetan culture as a large diversity of folksongs and dances,
hairstyles, dress designs impressed both the locals and the
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
"It is the first spectacular scene I have ever seen, even we
locals have not expected such a depth of folk dances with strong
flavor of Tibetan culture." said Duoji Cairang, who works in the
TAG Theatrical Company. "It has become the town's talk since the
opening ceremony rehearsal was held three days in advance."
</P>
<P>
"The ceremony was wonderful, fantastic, for the variety of folk
dances and songs." said Larry Nielsen, an ex-professor from the
United States who have toured a total of 56 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The deep impression on the spectators has made Danzen Gongbu
more confident of his road to boost the Tibetan culture.
</P>
<P>
"There are so many folk dances that even the locals have not
expected to watch. So this opening ceremony will be helpful to
give second thought to the Tibetan culture. "
</P>
<P>
Danzeng Gongbu, who began dancing at the age of 13 and has made
his mark in the research of Tibetan culture, said that for some
time the Tibetan culture has come to a crossroad where it faces
three choices.
</P>
<P>
"One is to remodel the local culture with the foreign school of
thought, secondly is to inherit the legacy without any change, the
last is to keep injecting new breath as remaining loyal to the
tradition."
</P>
<P>
"I keep to the last path which has been tested right in the
opening ceremony." said the official with the Culture Department
of the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
He was confident the opening ceremony has been a auspicious
omen to the Tibetan culture.
</P>
<P>
"It will help further protect and develop the ethnic culture
and provide an unprecedented window of opportunity for the
folklore." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
