<HEADLINE> Peruvian President Designates New Interior Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori
on Wednesday designated former defense minister General Cesar
Saucedo as interior minister.
</P>
<P>
With the designation of Saucedo, who took his oath for the new
position on the same day, Fujimori completed his ministerial
cabinet, where there had been not an interior minister since the
resignation of Victor Villanueva on July 24. Villanueva was named
as the General Commander of the Army and President of the Joint
Command of Armed Forces upon his resignation.
</P>
<P>
