LONDON, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The English Football Association
said on Wednesday that there is still a wide option on the F.A.
Cup final venue from 2001 while Wembley is being built.
</P>
<P>
There has been reports that Cardiff's new Millennium Stadium
will stage the game in the year of 2001.
</P>
<P>
F.A. spokesman Adrian Bevington said: "We could consider
Cardiff as an option but there is still a long period of time
before a decision has to be made."
</P>
<P>
Old Trafford, Villa Park, the Stadium of Light in Sunderland
and Twickenham, headquarters of English rugby union, are also
being considered as possible replacement venues.
</P>
<P>
Wembley has staged the F.A. Cup final since it was built in
1923. It is being demolished in the summer of 2000 and due to re-
open late in 2003.
</P>
<P>
Although not yet finished, the Millennium Stadium has already
staged rugby internationals and in October, for the start of the
rugby World Cup, it will have an all-seater capacity of 72,000
with a retractable roof.
</P>
<P>
Glanmor Griffiths, chairman of the Welsh rugby union and an
executive of the Millennium Stadium, said he would "compete
aggressively" to bring the F.A. Cup to Wales.
</P>
<P>
"We have an infrastructure in Cardiff to stage such events.We
are also looking to get the European Cup final in this stadium.
</P>
<P>
"We have the finest stadium in the world - there is no doubt
about that - and the F.A. Cup is not just for English clubs -three
teams from Wales compete in it, Cardiff City, Swansea City and
Wrexham.
</P>
<P>
"While our stadium was being built we staged six rugby
internationals at Wembley. We used their facilities -- now it's
time to reciprocate."
</P>
<P>
Cardiff City became the only Welsh club to win the F.A. Cup
when they beat Arsenal 1-0 at Wembley in 1927. They were also
beaten finalists in 1925.
</P>
<P>
The English League have also spoken to Welsh F.A. officials
about staging the League Cup final and the divisional promotion
play-offs at the Cardiff stadium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
