<HEADLINE> Seles Beats Panova for 5th Canadian Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles of the U.S. beat
Russian qualifier Tatiana Panova on Tuesday in a second-round
match of the $1.05 million du Maurier Open.
</P>
<P>
With a 6-7 (7-4), 6-1, 6-1 win over Panova at the National
Tennis Center in Toronto, the second-seed Seles has begun her
quest for a fifth straight Canadian Open title.
</P>
<P>
Seles made several unforced errors in the first set, but her
experience carried her through in the second and third sets of the
two hour and six-minute match.
</P>
<P>
"Today I wasn't going for my shots. Once I lost the first set I
started going for it more," she said after wearing down the 23-
year-old Panova.
</P>
<P>
She will meet 15th-seeded Elena Likhovsteva of Russia, who
eliminated Canada's top player Marreen Drake 6-0 and 7-5 in
another match on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
