<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed Wednesday with the Benchmark IPC index falling by 112.17
points, or 2.12 percent, to 5,167.72.
</P>
<P>
Dealers changed 38.947 milion shares for about 56.383 million
dollars against 72.99 million shares worth 89.372 million dollars
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, tha peso, stood at 9.45 to one dollar for
sale and 9.15 for purchase, compared with 9.50 for sale and 9.15
for purchase on the previous day, in the main exchange houses of
Mexico City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
